  "function_name": "_fit_transform",
  "justification": "This is the core fitting procedure for the FastICA class that performs Independent Component Analysis. The method takes a 2D array of shape (n_samples, n_features) and a boolean `compute_sources` parameter that controls whether to materialize the separated source matrix (returns array of shape (n_samples, n_components)) or only compute the rotation matrix (returns None) to save memory. The procedure includes: (1) validating and transposing input data (line 568-574), (2) selecting the nonlinearity function from logcosh, exp, cube, or user-supplied callable (lines 582-591), (3) determining n_components clamped to min(samples, features) (lines 599-605), (4) if whitening enabled, centering data and computing whitening matrix via eigendecomposition (eigh) or SVD (lines 607-639), (5) initializing unmixing weight matrix with random normal if not provided (lines 645-657), (6) delegating to either parallel symmetric decorrelation or deflation algorithm for iterative refinement (lines 667-670), (7) computing separated sources if requested (lines 675-681, 686), and (8) setting instance attributes for components_, mixing_, mean_, whitening_, _unmixing, and n_iter_ (lines 673, 691-698)."
}

